  "REGULATORY_EXAM_LETTER": {
    "description": "Regulatory examination correspondence — supervisory letter, examination report, matters requiring attention (MRA), matters requiring immediate attention (MRIA), or informal enforcement action correspondence. Issued by federal or state banking regulators (OCC, FDIC, Federal Reserve, CFPB, state DFS). Always routed to the Regulatory Change Management agent for tracking and response management.",
